'''Stairs To Spare''', otherwise known as '''Level 302''', is the 303<sup>rd</sup> level of the Backrooms.
== Description==

'''Level 302''' consists of many platforms in a space-like atmosphere at 20 levels of different heights, all floating and not supported by anything visible. The platforms are in a 10x10 grid, with some being quite different from the others. Examples of these are: being in a ruined-like state,  having rust on them, being in a different colour or continuously changing colours. However, most platforms are grey and do not have many distinctive features. No platforms, apart from visual, have any effects on them. 

When one first enters the level, they will be on one of the platforms but with no way of getting to the other platforms. After roughly 3 seconds however, stairs will start appearing from the bottom. The stairs will not have any effects on them at the start. The general layout of the stairs are randomly generated every time someone enters the level. Each platform will always have stairs to other platforms, however certain stairs may block other stairs, preventing one from reaching the platform above. This level also separates any 2 wanderers entering this level. 

Any items brought into this level will disappear until one exits this level, in which case the items will appear behind the wanderer's back. Since this happens, many wanderers end up starving to death. Many Almond Water bottles can be found scattered in this level however, making death by dehydration unlikely. 

The stairs can be moved by entities called "The Cubes", making traversing the level easier or harder depending on what effects are applied on the stairs by the ghosts. The Cubes colours may vary, which indicates which effect they inflict on stairs. Once one reaches the top, one will see The Orb. The Orb is a pink sphere with red rings surrounding it. Touching the orb will transport one to [[Level 798]]. The Orb will constantly move between platforms on the twentieth floor of platforms, making trying to wait for The Orb a viable option, but it may take a while. The Orb moves every 30 seconds.

=== Stair Effects ===
There are many effects that can be done to stairs, some examples being moved to other platforms, the stairs turning into a conveyer, the flight of stairs slowly turning invisible, the stairs turning 180 degrees and many more. There have been no confirmed total amount of effects on stairs, with 5 categories of effects currently having been discovered. There has been no case where 2 effects have happened on the same stairs. The Cubes can also change effects of stairs, turning the stairs from having 

Effects eventually wear off stairs once applied by the cubes, however this takes between 1 and 4 hours. The effect gradually gets weaker and the colour becomes fainter, however effects can also abruptly end. Weaker effects take a longer time to finish or may not even work. The table below shows the current categories known.  
