===Extravagant Effects===
Every once in a while, a "Extravagant Effect" happens. These effects affect most normal stairs on '''Level 302'''. One will get a 2 minute warning before the effect starts, indicated by the stairs flashing red and white, and a siren will happen as well. All current effects on all stairs will stop once the warning appears. After the 2 minute warning, all affected stairs will start to fall. Once this happens, new stairs will appear in their original locations with a certain effect, with red and blue being a exception. The stairs would be constantly moving if given a effect that affects the stair's movement. Fortunately, these effects have proven to be quite rare.

Among these extravagant effects can happen a "Scattered Event". These events, unlike a extravagant effect, affects all stairs. A Scattered event will typically consist of different levels of stairs being dealt with different effects. Effects that are in a Scattered Event may not be documented however, as the source of information may not be reliable, and they usually only happen once. In the case of one, it is advised to stay on a platform till the event is up. The event will likely be around 2 hours long.

===Level Value System===
There have been many items on certain platforms that have been confirmed to come from this level; including pots and [[Object 1|Almond Water]] bottles. Each level is given a "value", with this one's being 302. Most levels get values that correlate with their level's number. When one takes these items out of this level to a level attributed to a higher value, the item starts to glitch but one can still hold it. If brought to a level with a lower value, the item disappears entirely. All anomalous levels are given a value higher than 302. This does not apply to liquids, and there are certain levels which are exemptions, those being: 

*[[Level 111]], [[Level 115|115]] and [[Level 698|698]] where the item disappears like if bringing it to a lower number level.
*[[Level 798]], where the item stabilizes.
*[[Level 334]] and [[Level 502|502]],  where the item glitches but does not disappear.
[[Level 798]] could be considered "sister levels" to this level, as it may have the value "302" , or this level may have the value "798" as well. These values may be inaccurate, as these values are not stated. "302" has been used as a baseline value for these 2 levels. The level value sticks with the original's number, even when the current level's number gets changed or swapped.

===Reverse Stairs===
The "Reverse Stairs" have 40 levels of heights of platforms, in the same 10x10 grid. The connections between the platforms however are slopes instead of the normal stairs. The progression of these slopes are the direct opposite of the normal stairs, with it descending instead. However, walking off one of the slopes or platforms will cause one to float up to the top, where one will [[No-Clipping|No-Clip]] into [[Level 305]]. This area is filled with many fragments of stairs from the extravagant events, making this area dangerous to traverse. Objects are quite common in this sector, however they mainly block one's path. It is not recommended to go to this sector intentionally.  

The platforms and slopes are red, and there is no indication what effects a slope has. However, throwing a object on the slopes may help finding out the effect of the slopes. Slopes also move more frequently then it's counterpart, and slopes could have multiple effects at once. However, a slope having a effect is rarer than its normal counterpart. The platforms and slopes get more reddish the further one goes down. The slopes could also break off randomly, and platforms could outright disappear. There have also been more effects found in this sector, however none of these have been fully confirmed to happen. Below are some examples.
